00:42:56,740 --> 00:42:57,741
It's so good.

1212
00:42:57,825 --> 00:42:59,952
- The broth is great.
- There's some broth left.

1213
00:43:00,035 --> 00:43:01,537
Yeah, I'll be having seconds.

1214
00:43:01,620 --> 00:43:02,705
There's still plenty.

1215
00:43:04,164 --> 00:43:06,166
REFILL

1216
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:08,419
ANOTHER REFILL

1217
00:43:09,545 --> 00:43:12,590
- Jae-seong, I'm glad you like it.
- Thanks. It's good.

1218
00:43:12,673 --> 00:43:13,924
It's really good, you know?

1219
00:43:15,426 --> 00:43:17,886
- Kwang-soo did a wonderful job.
- Yeah.

1220
00:43:17,970 --> 00:43:20,306
- It's so good, seriously.
- That's our captain.

1221
00:43:20,889 --> 00:43:21,932
PROUD

1222
00:43:22,016 --> 00:43:23,183
I've never made it before.

1223
00:43:23,892 --> 00:43:26,478
This was my first time
ever making budae-jjigae,

1224
00:43:26,562 --> 00:43:28,022
and honestly, it was great.

1225
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:30,482
It might be the best dish
I've ever cooked.

1226
00:43:30,566 --> 00:43:31,900
I felt like a mom.

1227
00:43:31,984 --> 00:43:33,777
I was full just watching them.

1228
00:43:36,405 --> 00:43:38,991
And Woo-seok and Hyo-jung
made the gyeran-mari?

1229
00:43:39,074 --> 00:43:40,534
Wow, it's really…

1230
00:43:42,411 --> 00:43:44,079
Team Ye-eun did a great job.

1231
00:43:44,913 --> 00:43:46,415
Spicy broth in the rain is perfect.

1232
00:43:46,498 --> 00:43:47,833
Mmm, yeah, I know.

1233
00:43:48,959 --> 00:43:51,629
IT'S STILL RAINING OUTSIDE

1234
00:43:53,464 --> 00:43:55,257
I'm loving the rain.

1235
00:43:55,883 --> 00:43:58,260
- Me too. It's peaceful.
- Right?

1236
00:43:58,344 --> 00:44:00,804
Yeah, it's so nice
getting to listen to the rain.

1237
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:02,723
- Yeah, outside is great.
- I love it.

1238
00:44:05,934 --> 00:44:08,270
Not to pry,
but someone here is a chef, no?

1239
00:44:11,190 --> 00:44:13,025
There he goes.

1240
00:44:13,108 --> 00:44:14,109
I mean, there's got to be.

1241
00:44:14,193 --> 00:44:16,320
- That's straight up asking, isn't it?
- Yeah.

1242
00:44:16,403 --> 00:44:18,822
No, I was just talking to myself,
perhaps a bit loudly.

1243
00:44:18,906 --> 00:44:21,075
- Right, exactly. Nothing wrong with that.
- Oh, just talking to himself.

1244
00:44:21,158 --> 00:44:23,369
- But I bet there's a chef here.
- He's crazy.

1245
00:44:23,452 --> 00:44:24,662
There is a chef here.

1246
00:44:24,745 --> 00:44:26,372
Yeah. I can tell. Yeah.

1247
00:44:26,455 --> 00:44:28,457
- It seems like you're really curious.
- Sorry?

1248
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:29,833
- It seems like you're really curious.
- No.

1249
00:44:29,917 --> 00:44:32,002
He keeps guessing and asking questions.

1250
00:44:32,086 --> 00:44:33,587
No, I'm not interested.

1251
00:44:33,671 --> 00:44:37,508
I'm the kind of person who thinks
prying into other people's jobs is tacky.

1252
00:44:37,591 --> 00:44:40,135
I don't need to know who it is,
but if there is a chef,

1253
00:44:40,219 --> 00:44:42,721
draw a circle on a note
and put it in the suggestion box.

1254
00:44:42,805 --> 00:44:44,181
I just want to know if there is one.

1255
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:48,519
JOB GUESSING RADAR ACTIVATED

1256
00:44:48,602 --> 00:44:52,147
JUN-SEONG IS DOING THE DISHES
RIGHT AFTER EATING

1257
00:44:52,231 --> 00:44:54,525
Wow, look at Jun-seong
doing the dishes over there.

1258
00:44:54,608 --> 00:44:56,860
I have a feeling Jun-seong is a chef.

1259
00:44:57,528 --> 00:44:59,988
- That's not how a normal person works.
- Maybe he cooks part-time.

1260
00:45:00,072 --> 00:45:02,491
Whatever it is,
I noticed Jun-seong couldn't sit still.

1261
00:45:03,992 --> 00:45:05,786
I might be a bit more help
than my sisters.

1262
00:45:05,869 --> 00:45:07,705
CLUE 1. HE VOLUNTEERED TO HELP

1263
00:45:07,788 --> 00:45:09,498
CLUE 2.
HE NAILED THE RICE-WATER RATIO

1264
00:45:09,581 --> 00:45:12,084
CLUE 3.
HE CLEANED UP WHILE COOKING

1265
00:45:12,167 --> 00:45:14,753
- I've had a lot of chefs on my shows.
- Right.

1266
00:45:14,837 --> 00:45:16,630
One thing that I've learned about chefs

1267
00:45:16,714 --> 00:45:18,799
is that they clean up
right after they're done.

1268
00:45:18,882 --> 00:45:19,883
CHEFS CLEAN UP RIGHT AWAY

1269
00:45:19,967 --> 00:45:20,801
(AM I RIGHT?)

1270
00:45:20,884 --> 00:45:22,136
Maybe food service?

1271
00:45:22,219 --> 00:45:24,346
IS JUN-SEONG A CHEF?

1272
00:45:24,430 --> 00:45:26,473
Should we do our own dishes?

1273
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:27,599
- Should we?
- Sounds good.

1274
00:45:27,683 --> 00:45:29,476
- Let's do our own dishes.
- I was gonna do it.

1275
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:30,853
Just clean up after yourselves.

1276
00:45:30,936 --> 00:45:32,896
Or we could play a game
and have one person do it.

1277
00:45:32,980 --> 00:45:33,981
LOSER DOES ALL THE DISHES?

1278
00:45:34,064 --> 00:45:36,191
- You guys worked hard, so that'd be good.
- Should we do that?

1279
00:45:36,275 --> 00:45:37,818
You're having one person do it?

1280
00:45:37,901 --> 00:45:39,403
- That's not a bad idea.
- Do you want to?

1281
00:45:39,486 --> 00:45:40,487
Odd one out.

1282
00:45:40,571 --> 00:45:42,406
- The least common one is out.
- Two people.

1283
00:45:42,489 --> 00:45:43,532
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

1284
00:45:44,199 --> 00:45:45,951
- It's me. I'm out.
- Oh, man.

1285
00:45:46,535 --> 00:45:48,537
- The least common one.
- Ye-eun and…

1286
00:45:48,620 --> 00:45:49,663
shoot!

1287
00:45:49,747 --> 00:45:50,748
Let's go!

1288
00:45:50,831 --> 00:45:52,332
No, it's me, it's me.

1289
00:45:52,416 --> 00:45:53,500
HAPPY TO BE OFF DISH DUTY

1290
00:45:53,584 --> 00:45:54,668
Oh, man.

1291
00:45:54,752 --> 00:45:56,170
- Shoot!
- Yes!

1292
00:45:56,253 --> 00:45:57,254
- They're out.
- Two papers.

1293
00:45:57,337 --> 00:45:58,714
It's those two.

1294
00:45:58,797 --> 00:46:00,048
All right, your turn.

1295
00:46:00,549 --> 00:46:02,092
Shouldn't they play normal now?

1296
00:46:02,176 --> 00:46:03,177
- Yeah, normal rules.
- Normal rules.

1297
00:46:03,260 --> 00:46:04,261
NOW, THE REGULAR
ROCK-PAPER-SCISSORS

1298
00:46:04,344 --> 00:46:05,637
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

1299
00:46:05,721 --> 00:46:07,055
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

1300
00:46:07,139 --> 00:46:08,807
- All right!
- Yes!

1301
00:46:09,391 --> 00:46:10,559
Loser takes it all?

1302
00:46:10,642 --> 00:46:12,686
- Loser takes it all?
- Final round?

1303
00:46:13,187 --> 00:46:14,480
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

1304
00:46:15,606 --> 00:46:16,732
WOO-SEOK STUCK WITH
DISH DUTY FOR 8

1305
00:46:16,815 --> 00:46:18,692
- Oh, our captain.
- It's okay.

1306
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:20,110
- Captain.
- It's okay. I'll…

1307
00:46:20,694 --> 00:46:21,820
- Shoot!
- Yay!

1308
00:46:21,904 --> 00:46:22,905
DONG-GEON IS ON DISH DUTY

1309
00:46:22,988 --> 00:46:24,615
- Oh, no, I feel bad.
- No, I can't.

1310
00:46:24,698 --> 00:46:25,949
DONG-KYU & KYO-YOUNG
TAKE ON DISH DUTY

1311
00:46:26,033 --> 00:46:27,326
- We'll throw this out.
- Go get some rest.

1312
00:46:27,409 --> 00:46:28,494
- Okay.
- "Excellent."

1313
00:46:28,577 --> 00:46:29,995
THE WINNERS CAST THEIR
SATISFACTION VOTE AS THEY LEAVE

1314
00:46:30,078 --> 00:46:31,330
Another satisfactory.

1315
00:46:32,498 --> 00:46:33,957
I really enjoyed the meal, by the way.

1316
00:46:34,041 --> 00:46:35,667
- Yeah, I really enjoyed it too.
- I loved it.

1317
00:46:35,751 --> 00:46:37,544
- It was good, right?
- It was great.

1318
00:46:40,339 --> 00:46:43,217
- The dishes keep coming, huh?
- We'll wash these outside. The big ones.

1319
00:46:43,300 --> 00:46:45,803
THEY DECIDE TO DO
THE BIG WASHING-UP OUTSIDE

1320
00:46:45,886 --> 00:46:47,679
We're going to sleep well tonight.

1321
00:46:47,763 --> 00:46:49,014
- What?
- We're gonna sleep well.

1322
00:46:49,097 --> 00:46:50,349
Yeah, we'll pass out.

1323
00:46:50,432 --> 00:46:52,643
We don't even know
what's happening in the world.

1324
00:46:53,143 --> 00:46:54,436
You're right.

1325
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:56,980
- We're not even checking our phones.
- We don't have time for that.

1326
00:46:57,689 --> 00:46:59,733
Other than what should we eat next,

1327
00:46:59,817 --> 00:47:01,360
- and what do we do next…
- Right.

1328
00:47:01,443 --> 00:47:03,654
- …there's nothing else to think about.
- Right.

1329
00:47:06,573 --> 00:47:08,033
Oh, my back.

1330
00:47:09,618 --> 00:47:12,287
GROANING

1331
00:47:18,544 --> 00:47:20,003
Seriously, my whole body hurts.

1332
00:47:20,087 --> 00:47:21,880
I feel like I got run over.

1333
00:47:21,964 --> 00:47:23,465
Well, we're all done.

1334
00:47:23,549 --> 00:47:25,050
BODIES FEEL LIKE LEAD

1335
00:47:25,133 --> 00:47:26,593
Let's clean up the floor real quick.

1336
00:47:26,677 --> 00:47:28,637
- Okay.
- Hey, Chief Yu, I was wondering,

1337
00:47:28,720 --> 00:47:30,848
do we have any beer or anything?

1338
00:47:30,931 --> 00:47:32,224
Oh, beer?

1339
00:47:33,225 --> 00:47:34,643
Well, we didn't buy any.

1340
00:47:35,185 --> 00:47:37,771
I mean, I'm not asking for myself.
I don't…

1341
00:47:37,855 --> 00:47:38,939
Okay, so you want beer.

1342
00:47:40,732 --> 00:47:41,775
KWANG-SOO'S TAKING
A QUICK WATER BREAK

1343
00:47:41,859 --> 00:47:43,151
Okay, so you want beer. All right.

1344
00:47:45,237 --> 00:47:46,822
Kwang-soo, beer…

1345
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:49,116
Could you…

1346
00:47:49,199 --> 00:47:50,993
- Get the mop.
- Do you want me to run out and get some?

1347
00:47:51,076 --> 00:47:52,995
No, no, the store is quite far from here.

1348
00:47:53,078 --> 00:47:54,997
Oh, well, we could take the car.

1349
00:47:55,080 --> 00:47:58,292
No, no, you could,
but I'll go get it. It's fine.

1350
00:47:58,375 --> 00:48:00,210
- Could you mop this up?
- Okay.

1351
00:48:00,294 --> 00:48:02,004
- Not a problem. I'll finish cleaning up.
- Okay.

1352
00:48:02,588 --> 00:48:04,506
I actually thought about getting
some beer, but I didn't.

1353
00:48:04,590 --> 00:48:05,841
I SHOULD'VE KNOWN BETTER

1354
00:48:06,717 --> 00:48:07,718
Wait.

1355
00:48:08,635 --> 00:48:09,636
One sec.

1356
00:48:10,596 --> 00:48:11,597
Ah, it's wet.

1357
00:48:11,680 --> 00:48:12,723
RUSHING

1358
00:48:12,806 --> 00:48:14,099
- Chief Yu.
- Yeah?

1359
00:48:14,182 --> 00:48:16,018
Were you only planning on getting beer?

1360
00:48:16,101 --> 00:48:18,478
Because I actually brought
a small bottle of soju.

1361
00:48:18,562 --> 00:48:19,938
You brought soju?

1362
00:48:20,022 --> 00:48:21,440
A FEW MINUTES EARLIER

1363
00:48:22,024 --> 00:48:23,191
I brought some booze.

1364
00:48:23,275 --> 00:48:25,068
Really?

1365
00:48:25,152 --> 00:48:26,695
- It's soju, 24%.
- No way.

1366
00:48:26,778 --> 00:48:27,946
I picked it up on a trip.

1367
00:48:28,030 --> 00:48:30,198
- Now I feel bad I didn't bring anything.
- Oh, it's fine.

1368
00:48:30,282 --> 00:48:31,283
JOO-HYUN BROUGHT DRINKS TO SHARE

1369
00:48:31,366 --> 00:48:34,494
But considering how many of us there are,
it might be good to have some more.

1370
00:48:34,578 --> 00:48:36,830
- More soju? Oh, all right.
- Yeah, okay.

1371
00:48:36,914 --> 00:48:37,915
SOJU, GOT IT

1372
00:48:37,998 --> 00:48:40,542
Yeah, some drinks.
I did think about that earlier.

1373
00:48:41,919 --> 00:48:44,588
EXHAUSTED

1374
00:48:44,671 --> 00:48:46,506
Ye-eun, you know a lot
about alcohol, right?

1375
00:48:46,590 --> 00:48:47,591
Well…

1376
00:48:47,674 --> 00:48:50,010
Joo-hyun is crazy.
She ran up to us in the rain

1377
00:48:50,093 --> 00:48:51,845
and asked us to grab more soju.

1378
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:53,055
- Oh, really?
- Mm.

1379
00:48:53,138 --> 00:48:55,724
That girl's something else.

1380
00:48:55,807 --> 00:48:57,434
I mean, it makes me curious.

1381
00:48:57,517 --> 00:48:58,977
I'M SO CURIOUS ABOUT
THESE PEOPLE

1382
00:48:59,061 --> 00:49:00,228
It's driving me crazy.

1383
00:49:02,522 --> 00:49:04,399
The funny thing about this is

1384
00:49:04,483 --> 00:49:06,526
- even though we all have different jobs…
- Yeah.

1385
00:49:06,610 --> 00:49:08,904
…and I don't even know
how old everyone is,

1386
00:49:08,987 --> 00:49:11,573
when we played that game,
I realized we're all the same.

1387
00:49:11,657 --> 00:49:12,824
- Yeah, of course.
- Yeah.

1388
00:49:12,908 --> 00:49:14,993
It felt like we went straight back
to our childhood.

1389
00:49:15,077 --> 00:49:16,078
- To being kids.
- Yeah.

1390
00:49:16,161 --> 00:49:18,956
- That's right.
- But if we'd known what everyone did,

1391
00:49:19,039 --> 00:49:21,875
how old they were, I don't think
we could have connected like that.

1392
00:49:21,959 --> 00:49:22,960
Hmm.

1393
00:49:23,043 --> 00:49:26,505
Like, for example,
if someone was a company CEO,

1394
00:49:26,588 --> 00:49:28,966
or really young,
or there was a big age gap,

1395
00:49:29,049 --> 00:49:31,301
it would have been harder to talk to them.

1396
00:49:31,385 --> 00:49:32,844
- Totally.
- You're right, you're right.

1397
00:49:33,470 --> 00:49:35,180
Everyone seemed like they were having fun.

1398
00:49:35,263 --> 00:49:36,431
I know.

1399
00:49:36,515 --> 00:49:38,266
Hey, I didn't even have time to call home.

1400
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:40,352
Wow, Jae-seok, seriously…

1401
00:49:41,478 --> 00:49:42,854
How do you live like this?

1402
00:49:43,355 --> 00:49:45,899
- What do you mean? Live like what?
- I mean, you work every day.

1403
00:49:45,983 --> 00:49:49,528
Like, every single day,
but you don't have any free time.

1404
00:49:49,611 --> 00:49:51,029
- Eventually…
- Yeah?

1405
00:49:51,613 --> 00:49:52,948
…everyone becomes free.

1406
00:49:53,031 --> 00:49:54,282
And then you'll miss this time.

1407
00:49:55,784 --> 00:49:56,910
Still, it's amazing.

1408
00:49:58,620 --> 00:49:59,621
I can take that.

1409
00:49:59,705 --> 00:50:00,580
MEANWHILE AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

1410
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:01,665
- All right, thanks.
- Here.

1411
00:50:01,748 --> 00:50:03,083
MORE DISHES

1412
00:50:03,166 --> 00:50:05,460
- This too, please.
- Okay.

1413
00:50:05,544 --> 00:50:07,045
MORE DISHES

1414
00:50:07,129 --> 00:50:08,588
A PILE OF DISHES

1415
00:50:08,672 --> 00:50:10,757
- Well, I feel bad. Yeah.
- I know.

1416
00:50:11,383 --> 00:50:13,885
There are too many cups and plates.

1417
00:50:13,969 --> 00:50:16,430
All right, I'll… I'll wash them.

1418
00:50:16,930 --> 00:50:18,849
It's really okay.
You should get some rest.

1419
00:50:18,932 --> 00:50:21,768
Let me wash. You can rinse.
I've got nothing to do.

1420
00:50:21,852 --> 00:50:23,854
All right. We can do it together.

1421
00:50:23,937 --> 00:50:25,772
We're a team. We're on the same team.

1422
00:50:25,856 --> 00:50:27,232
Thanks for helping.

1423
00:50:27,315 --> 00:50:28,734
- I had so much fun playing the game.
- Yeah.

1424
00:50:28,817 --> 00:50:30,527
- I totally lost track of time.
- It's a shame.

1425
00:50:30,610 --> 00:50:33,071
Three days and two nights
is way too short.

1426
00:50:33,155 --> 00:50:35,365
I know. It's already been a whole day.

1427
00:50:37,451 --> 00:50:39,536
- It will be a great memory.
- Right.

1428
00:50:39,619 --> 00:50:41,621
I hope everyone feels the same way.

1429
00:50:42,581 --> 00:50:45,333
I think I would want to come back too.

1430
00:50:45,417 --> 00:50:49,379
I mean, something like this
doesn't happen very often, you know?

1431
00:50:49,880 --> 00:50:51,798
You're right. Totally.

1432
00:50:52,799 --> 00:50:54,134
- You know…
- Hmm?

1433
00:50:54,843 --> 00:50:57,429
…this weekend, it feels like a dream.

1434
00:50:57,512 --> 00:50:58,722
It feels like a dream.

1435
00:50:59,389 --> 00:51:01,349
- What do you mean?
- This whole thing.

1436
00:51:01,433 --> 00:51:02,517
It feels like I'm dreaming.

1437
00:51:03,935 --> 00:51:05,479
Hearing you say that…

1438
00:51:06,605 --> 00:51:08,356
it makes me really happy.

1439
00:51:12,194 --> 00:51:15,697
- You know…
- This just makes me happy too.

1440
00:51:16,281 --> 00:51:17,616
Uh…

1441
00:51:17,699 --> 00:51:19,076
I want you even happier.

1442
00:51:25,874 --> 00:51:29,377
When she told me
that this moment felt like a dream to her,

1443
00:51:30,295 --> 00:51:31,671
every word she said…

1444
00:51:32,756 --> 00:51:36,843
just really, you know,
hit me right in the heart.

1445
00:51:39,638 --> 00:51:41,389
Hearing that made me really happy.

1446
00:51:45,143 --> 00:51:47,104
- I hope while we're here…
- Mm?

1447
00:51:47,187 --> 00:51:49,397
…we can make a few more
fantastic memories for you.

1448
00:51:49,481 --> 00:51:51,108
That sounds amazing. I'd love that.

1449
00:51:52,359 --> 00:51:54,069
I'll be really sad when this is over.

1450
00:51:57,155 --> 00:51:58,532
Are you gonna have a beer?

1451
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:00,450
Me? No, I'll just have a coffee.

1452
00:52:00,534 --> 00:52:02,327
- You don't drink at all? Oh, really?
- No.

1453
00:52:02,410 --> 00:52:04,704
I used to drink, but not anymore.

1454
00:52:04,788 --> 00:52:06,289
It can't be easy to hold back.

1455
00:52:07,124 --> 00:52:09,793
By the way,
you look like a trot singer right now.

1456
00:52:12,129 --> 00:52:14,506
A trot singer waiting to go on stage.

1457
00:52:15,090 --> 00:52:16,675
A trot singer? I like that.

1458
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:19,302
Well, I got nothing to do.
I'll mop the floor.

1459
00:52:19,386 --> 00:52:23,014
CLEANING DILIGENTLY WHILE
THE STAFF IS OUT BUYING BEER

1460
00:52:23,598 --> 00:52:25,517
CLEANING DONE

1461
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:26,685
They went to buy beer.

1462
00:52:26,768 --> 00:52:28,520
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1463
00:52:28,603 --> 00:52:30,564
- Oh, that's great.
- Beer sounds amazing.

1464
00:52:30,647 --> 00:52:32,315
Oh, the detective's here. The detective.

1465
00:52:32,399 --> 00:52:34,568
- Detective, detective.
- How did you know?

1466
00:52:35,068 --> 00:52:36,069
- Detective.
- Huh?

1467
00:52:36,153 --> 00:52:37,654
- Are you a cop?
- He's a cop?

1468
00:52:37,737 --> 00:52:38,738
- Are you a cop?
- Seriously?

1469
00:52:38,822 --> 00:52:40,031
No, it's about Mafia.

1470
00:52:40,115 --> 00:52:41,658
- Really?
- For real?

1471
00:52:41,741 --> 00:52:42,868
- Are you serious?
- No, no.

1472
00:52:42,951 --> 00:52:44,452
- Like in real life?
- Maybe he is.

1473
00:52:44,536 --> 00:52:45,996
So, not just in Mafia?

1474
00:52:46,079 --> 00:52:47,581
Maybe he's really a detective.

1475
00:52:47,664 --> 00:52:49,166
He does have that vibe.

1476
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:51,710
You mean the detective in Mafia, right?
You surprised me.

1477
00:52:51,793 --> 00:52:54,337
- I think he might be a detective.
- He said, "How did you know?"

1478
00:52:55,338 --> 00:52:56,631
"I pledge."

1479
00:52:56,715 --> 00:52:57,966
(RIGHT ON THE BEAT)
"I PLEDGE"

1480
00:52:58,049 --> 00:52:59,426
CRISP AND PROPER

1481
00:53:00,302 --> 00:53:02,846
HE GOT THE LAY OF THE LAND
AS SOON AS HE ARRIVED

1482
00:53:05,807 --> 00:53:07,350
Oh, so we got sleeping bags too.

1483
00:53:08,018 --> 00:53:09,644
That's a barbecue. There are gloves too.

1484
00:53:09,728 --> 00:53:10,896
A THOROUGH FIELD INVESTIGATION

1485
00:53:12,063 --> 00:53:15,025
WHAT'S JAE-HYEONG'S
TRUE IDENTITY?

1486
00:53:15,108 --> 00:53:17,611
- I think those two are designers.
- Designers?

1487
00:53:17,694 --> 00:53:18,945
DESIGNERS?

1488
00:53:19,029 --> 00:53:22,240
No, I think they're dancers.
I think they're dancers.

1489
00:53:22,324 --> 00:53:23,909
No, that would be too obvious.

1490
00:53:23,992 --> 00:53:25,869
- Too obvious.
- You think so?

1491
00:53:25,952 --> 00:53:27,662
THEY MADE ONE FLASHY ENTRANCE

1492
00:53:28,246 --> 00:53:29,414
We even coordinated.

1493
00:53:32,626 --> 00:53:34,211
- Honestly, I really like our last outfit.
- Me too.

1494
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:35,295
ARE THEY FASHION DESIGNERS?

1495
00:53:35,378 --> 00:53:36,338
Do the shuffle.

1496
00:53:36,421 --> 00:53:37,297
OR

1497
00:53:38,256 --> 00:53:40,050
- Two, three, bam!
- That's it.

1498
00:53:40,550 --> 00:53:42,594
WHAT DO JUN-HYUK & HYO-LIM DO?

1499
00:53:42,677 --> 00:53:44,137
- Look who's here.
- What about hairdressers?

1500
00:53:44,221 --> 00:53:46,139
- A stylist? I can see that.
- Are we guessing jobs?

1501
00:53:46,223 --> 00:53:47,557
Yeah.

1502
00:53:47,641 --> 00:53:48,892
Should I leave?

1503
00:53:48,975 --> 00:53:50,727
Something tells me you're an actor.

1504
00:53:51,519 --> 00:53:53,897
- That's right.
- I'm thinking about trying it, actually.

1505
00:53:54,522 --> 00:53:55,523
This is great.

1506
00:53:55,607 --> 00:53:58,818
If there's anything you don't like,
just drop it in the suggestion box

1507
00:53:58,902 --> 00:54:00,278
- and we'll take it into account.
- Great.

1508
00:54:00,362 --> 00:54:02,822
Well, trash cans might be nice
in our dorms.

1509
00:54:02,906 --> 00:54:04,241
Oh, there are no trash cans?

1510
00:54:04,324 --> 00:54:05,533
Since they're at the store…

1511
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:08,745
Hey, Hyung.

1512
00:54:09,246 --> 00:54:12,916
They're saying there are no trash cans
in the dorm.

1513
00:54:12,999 --> 00:54:14,459
<i>Think you can pick some up?</i>

1514
00:54:15,460 --> 00:54:17,379
- Oh, trash cans.
- Will they have those?

1515
00:54:18,296 --> 00:54:20,048
Oh, okay, we should get some.

1516
00:54:20,131 --> 00:54:21,591
Let's see. Trash cans…

1517
00:54:23,385 --> 00:54:24,928
- Oh, here they are.
- Where?

1518
00:54:25,011 --> 00:54:27,722
- Oh, this is perfect.
- Very good.

1519
00:54:27,806 --> 00:54:30,558
- Hyung, I'm getting beer.
- Go ahead. Grab it.

1520
00:54:30,642 --> 00:54:33,103
Should we get some apple juice
and one of these as well?

1521
00:54:33,186 --> 00:54:35,605
- While we're at it.
- So two boxes of green grapes?

1522
00:54:35,689 --> 00:54:36,690
Two? These are good.

1523
00:54:36,773 --> 00:54:37,774
MIGHT AS WELL GET YOGURT TOO

1524
00:54:37,857 --> 00:54:39,651
- Isn't that too much?
- This should be enough.

1525
00:54:39,734 --> 00:54:41,736
Look. Snacks to go with the drinks.
Not bad, right?

1526
00:54:41,820 --> 00:54:42,821
Thank you, sir.

1527
00:54:42,904 --> 00:54:43,905
- Thank you.
- Good night.

1528
00:54:43,989 --> 00:54:45,198
DAY 1 FINAL GROCERY RUN

1529
00:54:46,700 --> 00:54:48,159
Hey, the rain's really picking up.

1530
00:54:48,743 --> 00:54:49,995
It's really coming down.

1531
00:54:50,078 --> 00:54:51,329
- They're back.
- Oh?

1532
00:54:52,789 --> 00:54:55,083
Oh. Everyone's waiting for the drinks.

1533
00:54:55,166 --> 00:54:56,209
All right.

1534
00:54:58,336 --> 00:55:00,422
- I'm sorry to trouble you.
- Hey, it's no trouble.

1535
00:55:00,505 --> 00:55:01,840
Well, it came up
while we've been chatting.

1536
00:55:01,923 --> 00:55:03,133
Oh, you've been chatting?

1537
00:55:03,216 --> 00:55:04,843
Go inside. You're getting wet.

1538
00:55:04,926 --> 00:55:06,094
Oh, soju, soju, soju.

1539
00:55:06,177 --> 00:55:07,721
- We've got makgeolli.
- All right, makgeolli!

1540
00:55:07,804 --> 00:55:09,014
TRASH CANS CLEANED
BEFORE DELIVERY

1541
00:55:09,097 --> 00:55:10,098
Okay.

1542
00:55:10,849 --> 00:55:12,767
- Were you chatting instead of cleaning?
- Us?

1543
00:55:12,851 --> 00:55:14,519
- We talked the whole time.
- We sat there and…

1544
00:55:14,602 --> 00:55:16,855
I see, but you don't know everything
about each other, right?

1545
00:55:16,938 --> 00:55:18,273
No, not yet.

1546
00:55:18,773 --> 00:55:19,858
- Kwang-soo.
- Yes?

1547
00:55:19,941 --> 00:55:21,735
- You curious too?
- It's killing me.

1548
00:55:22,319 --> 00:55:23,820
There's three people I want to know about.

1549
00:55:23,903 --> 00:55:24,904
Three?

1550
00:55:24,988 --> 00:55:27,198
I said I wasn't curious,
but I can't help it.

1551
00:55:27,282 --> 00:55:28,408
Gotta ask questions.

1552
00:55:28,491 --> 00:55:29,993
- Right, yeah.
- Yeah, you asked if there was chef.

1553
00:55:30,076 --> 00:55:32,078
- It's like we're playing 20 Questions.
- Yeah.

1554
00:55:32,162 --> 00:55:33,747
- Mark my words…
- Just a few clues here and there.

1555
00:55:33,830 --> 00:55:36,207
…one of them is a chef, I'm telling you.

1556
00:55:36,291 --> 00:55:38,626
- That's not easy to do, you know?
- Cleaning up like that is a giveaway.

1557
00:55:38,710 --> 00:55:39,961
ABSOLUTE CERTAINTY

1558
00:55:40,045 --> 00:55:41,087
Okay.

1559
00:55:41,588 --> 00:55:43,131
- Where's the restaurant?
- Sorry?

1560
00:55:44,632 --> 00:55:45,633
Where's the restaurant?

1561
00:55:46,301 --> 00:55:47,761
- Restaurant?
- Restaurant?

1562
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:49,220
- It's right here.
- Right here.

1563
00:55:49,304 --> 00:55:50,347
The one you run.

1564
00:55:50,430 --> 00:55:51,765
Me? I don't run one.

1565
00:55:51,848 --> 00:55:53,600
Oh, you don't?

1566
00:55:53,683 --> 00:55:55,518
Well, I guess we were wrong.

1567
00:55:56,019 --> 00:55:57,771
- Why do you keep asking?
- Sorry. I'm sorry.

1568
00:55:57,854 --> 00:55:59,481
I thought you might slip up.

1569
00:56:01,274 --> 00:56:03,068
We're gonna take a second
to check out our rooms.

1570
00:56:03,151 --> 00:56:04,152
- See you later.
- See you.

1571
00:56:04,235 --> 00:56:05,236
9:30 P.M. STAFF REGROUPING

1572
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:06,571
Get some rest.

1573
00:56:06,654 --> 00:56:08,573
- Did you take a shower?
- Yes, I did.

1574
00:56:08,656 --> 00:56:09,657
Is the water nice?

1575
00:56:09,741 --> 00:56:10,825
- It was perfect.
- It's great.

1576
00:56:10,909 --> 00:56:11,993
- Nice and hot?
- Yes.

1577
00:56:12,077 --> 00:56:13,578
- It was great.
- Good, good.

1578
00:56:14,746 --> 00:56:17,582
Wait, where are my shoes? "Yu Jae-seok."

1579
00:56:17,665 --> 00:56:18,917
Oh, these aren't mine.

1580
00:56:19,000 --> 00:56:20,001
"YU JAE-SEOK" EVERYWHERE

1581
00:56:20,085 --> 00:56:22,087
Shoot, wait. "Yu Jae-seok." Here they are.

1582
00:56:23,671 --> 00:56:25,507
We need to take the registration forms.

1583
00:56:25,590 --> 00:56:26,591
Yeah.

1584
00:56:26,674 --> 00:56:28,385
HE PICKS UP
THE REGISTRATION FORMS

1585
00:56:29,386 --> 00:56:30,470
Oh, there's a lot.

1586
00:56:30,553 --> 00:56:32,931
AND CHECKS THE SUGGESTION BOX

1587
00:56:33,515 --> 00:56:35,767
Wait, this the first time
we're going to the staff quarters

1588
00:56:35,850 --> 00:56:37,894
since dropping off our luggage.

1589
00:56:38,478 --> 00:56:40,271
That's right. The other way, hyung.

1590
00:56:40,355 --> 00:56:42,107
Oh, right. My gosh.

1591
00:56:42,857 --> 00:56:43,858
Damn.

1592
00:56:43,942 --> 00:56:46,569
FEELING THE EFFECTS
OF THE 14-HOUR SHIFT

1593
00:56:48,029 --> 00:56:50,448
Jeez. Oh, man.

1594
00:56:51,157 --> 00:56:52,575
Hey, good work.

1595
00:56:53,326 --> 00:56:55,620
GROANS AND SIGHS EVERYWHERE

1596
00:56:56,204 --> 00:56:57,705
CHUCKLING

1597
00:56:57,789 --> 00:56:59,749
- Seriously.
- Huh?

1598
00:56:59,833 --> 00:57:01,292
I'm just so wiped.

1599
00:57:02,710 --> 00:57:04,921
This might've been
the most hectic day of my life.

1600
00:57:05,004 --> 00:57:06,089
Man, seriously.

1601
00:57:06,172 --> 00:57:07,966
I really want to go to sleep.

1602
00:57:08,049 --> 00:57:09,300
Tell me about it.

1603
00:57:11,386 --> 00:57:13,680
LOADING UP ON SUPPLEMENTS

1604
00:57:13,763 --> 00:57:14,806
Seriously.

1605
00:57:14,889 --> 00:57:17,183
AN EXHAUSTED YE-EUN

1606
00:57:18,351 --> 00:57:21,020
ALSO GROANS ON HER WAY BACK
TO HER ROOM

1607
00:57:26,776 --> 00:57:27,777
Dong-geon.

1608
00:57:27,861 --> 00:57:29,946
- Dong-geon.
- Yes?

1609
00:57:30,488 --> 00:57:31,781
Is there any water?

1610
00:57:32,490 --> 00:57:33,950
Bring me a bottle.

1611
00:57:36,161 --> 00:57:38,872
LOTION ON HOLD FOR A WATER RUN

1612
00:57:42,959 --> 00:57:43,960
Thank you.

1613
00:57:44,669 --> 00:57:46,921
ORDERED AROUND
EVEN OUTSIDE OF HIS HOME

1614
00:57:47,005 --> 00:57:49,757
- Staff, let's get washed up first.
- Yeah.

1615
00:57:49,841 --> 00:57:50,842
LET'S GO WASH UP

1616
00:57:50,925 --> 00:57:52,469
- All right, we'll be back.
- See you in a bit.

1617
00:57:53,052 --> 00:57:54,137
WHILE THE STAFF FRESHENS UP

1618
00:57:54,679 --> 00:57:58,725
THE GUESTS WASH UP
AND START GATHERING ONE BY ONE

1619
00:58:00,727 --> 00:58:03,021
(HOVERING)

1620
00:58:04,189 --> 00:58:06,691
I don't think there's enough room
for me to get in there.

1621
00:58:08,485 --> 00:58:11,529
CORNER BED NOT EASY TO GET INTO

1622
00:58:11,613 --> 00:58:14,032
I think we may have picked the wrong spot.

1623
00:58:14,115 --> 00:58:15,533
Exactly.

1624
00:58:16,117 --> 00:58:18,620
THEY DECIDE TO MOVE THEIR BEDS

1625
00:58:18,703 --> 00:58:19,704
You know what?

1626
00:58:19,787 --> 00:58:22,415
It might actually be fun
to take this out and sleep outside.

1627
00:58:23,958 --> 00:58:25,960
EUN-TAE JOINS THE BED MOVE

1628
00:58:26,044 --> 00:58:27,712
Should we put all our beds together?

1629
00:58:27,795 --> 00:58:29,297
Why not?

1630
00:58:29,380 --> 00:58:31,466
Should we move them all to the center?

1631
00:58:31,966 --> 00:58:34,135
Yeah, this way we can all talk.

1632
00:58:34,219 --> 00:58:35,428
Well, isn't this nice?

1633
00:58:38,806 --> 00:58:40,808
EVERYONE'S MOVING THEIR BEDS

1634
00:58:41,518 --> 00:58:43,686
(TWIRL)

1635
00:58:43,770 --> 00:58:45,522
Hey, you know what? This is kind of fun.

1636
00:58:46,147 --> 00:58:47,774
It feels like a parade.

1637
00:58:47,857 --> 00:58:49,108
LIKE A SCENE FROM A PARADE

1638
00:58:56,115 --> 00:58:57,158
Like this?

1639
00:58:57,242 --> 00:58:58,243
A little more.

1640
00:58:58,826 --> 00:59:00,912
- Here?
- That's good, that's good. Stop, stop.

1641
00:59:01,955 --> 00:59:04,582
This is a special,
once-in-a-lifetime experience.

1642
00:59:04,666 --> 00:59:05,667
There.

1643
00:59:05,750 --> 00:59:07,085
- There.
- Looks good.

1644
00:59:07,168 --> 00:59:08,503
Looks good.

1645
00:59:08,586 --> 00:59:09,587
You sure about this?

1646
00:59:09,671 --> 00:59:11,381
ARE WE REALLY SLEEPING
LIKE THIS?

1647
00:59:12,549 --> 00:59:14,425
It looks like we're here
for a clinical trial.

1648
00:59:15,468 --> 00:59:16,719
Are you having beer?

1649
00:59:16,803 --> 00:59:18,221
- Are they going now?
- Yeah.

1650
00:59:18,304 --> 00:59:19,681
Let's get it.

1651
00:59:19,764 --> 00:59:21,140
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1652
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:22,725
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

1653
00:59:22,809 --> 00:59:24,185
Let's get it.

1654
00:59:24,269 --> 00:59:26,646
THE STAFF ARE BACK
FROM THEIR SHOWERS

1655
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:32,360
Here. Space them out, will you?

1656
00:59:33,695 --> 00:59:35,196
I hope nobody snores.

1657
00:59:35,280 --> 00:59:36,614
SPACED OUT

1658
00:59:37,532 --> 00:59:39,325
SPACED OUT

1659
00:59:40,493 --> 00:59:43,746
FINISHING UP WITH HIS HYUNG

1660
00:59:45,540 --> 00:59:46,541
Oh, a bed.

1661
00:59:47,166 --> 00:59:49,711
TOTALLY WIPED OUT

1662
00:59:49,794 --> 00:59:51,296
Seriously though…

1663
00:59:54,048 --> 00:59:55,758
You worked so hard today.

1664
00:59:56,342 --> 00:59:57,510
You too.

1665
00:59:57,594 --> 00:59:58,720
Seriously. Wow.

1666
00:59:59,220 --> 01:00:01,347
This was the toughest day ever.

1667
01:00:01,848 --> 01:00:03,933
I mean, we didn't take any breaks.

1668
01:00:05,310 --> 01:00:06,352
That's true.

1669
01:00:06,978 --> 01:00:08,104
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!

1670
01:00:08,938 --> 01:00:09,939
RECEPTION PREP

1671
01:00:10,023 --> 01:00:11,274
- Can we do the towels?
- We don't have time.

1672
01:00:11,357 --> 01:00:14,235
I'll hold nothing back, talk nonstop,
and play hard to my heart's content.

1673
01:00:14,319 --> 01:00:15,612
ORIENTATION
LUNCH PREP AND LUNCH

1674
01:00:15,695 --> 01:00:16,696
What the heck are you doing?

1675
01:00:16,779 --> 01:00:17,822
COFFEE PICKUP

1676
01:00:17,905 --> 01:00:19,198
- Did it all spill?
- No!

1677
01:00:19,282 --> 01:00:20,575
THE CUSHION QUIZ

1678
01:00:20,658 --> 01:00:21,659
- Got it!
- Got it!

1679
01:00:21,743 --> 01:00:23,244
That's like something
you'd get at a restaurant.

1680
01:00:23,328 --> 01:00:24,871
- I'm getting beer.
- Go ahead, grab it.

1681
01:00:24,954 --> 01:00:26,164
DINNER
GROCERY RUN

1682
01:00:26,247 --> 01:00:27,707
PRESENT
ALL OF THIS HAPPENED IN ONE DAY

1683
01:00:27,790 --> 01:00:31,669
We came here at 9:00 a.m.
and haven't had a break since.

1684
01:00:32,170 --> 01:00:34,547
Except for the shower just now.

1685
01:00:34,631 --> 01:00:36,507
The only break I had the whole day

1686
01:00:37,300 --> 01:00:39,302
was the 30 seconds I had to pee.

1687
01:00:39,802 --> 01:00:41,804
My phone battery's still at 85%.

1688
01:00:41,888 --> 01:00:43,473
That never happens.

1689
01:00:44,474 --> 01:00:47,935
- Also, it's not just the three of us here.
- Right.

1690
01:00:48,019 --> 01:00:50,480
We're with people we don't know,
and it feels more…

1691
01:00:50,563 --> 01:00:52,649
- You're more aware.
- Yeah, you're more aware.

1692
01:00:52,732 --> 01:00:54,692
- You want to be on your best behavior.
- Yeah.

1693
01:00:54,776 --> 01:00:56,110
That's true.

1694
01:00:56,194 --> 01:00:57,945
OUR DEAR GUESTS

1695
01:00:58,029 --> 01:01:00,156
Hyung, it's one minute until lights out.

1696
01:01:00,948 --> 01:01:02,450
Those who want to sleep can sleep.

1697
01:01:04,035 --> 01:01:05,036
Huh?

1698
01:01:05,536 --> 01:01:06,788
Where is everyone? Huh?

1699
01:01:09,374 --> 01:01:10,958
Wait, it's supposed to be lights out.

1700
01:01:11,042 --> 01:01:12,293
We have to make the announcement…

1701
01:01:12,377 --> 01:01:13,711
Wait. We, uh…

1702
01:01:13,795 --> 01:01:16,756
Well, the thing is,
since it's only three days and two nights…

1703
01:01:16,839 --> 01:01:18,216
You're right. Yeah.

1704
01:01:18,299 --> 01:01:19,676
There they are. There.

1705
01:01:19,759 --> 01:01:21,302
- Look, everyone's over there.
- Aren't they tired?

1706
01:01:21,386 --> 01:01:22,387
They're all…

1707
01:01:23,638 --> 01:01:25,848
- Uh…
- Some of them don't drink, but…

1708
01:01:25,932 --> 01:01:27,266
All right, everyone.

1709
01:01:28,142 --> 01:01:30,019
No one's here.

1710
01:01:30,103 --> 01:01:31,604
What kind of announcement…

1711
01:01:31,688 --> 01:01:33,856
- Who are you talking to?
- This is embarrassing.

1712
01:01:33,940 --> 01:01:35,858
They could've at least stayed
until the announcement.

1713
01:01:35,942 --> 01:01:37,276
- I mean…
- Yeah, nobody's there.

1714
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:40,571
They could've stayed
until the announcement. Where did they go?

1715
01:01:40,655 --> 01:01:41,823
Where did they go?

1716
01:01:41,906 --> 01:01:42,907
THEY CAN STILL HEAR HIM

1717
01:01:42,990 --> 01:01:45,451
- It's lights out.
- We're over here.

1718
01:01:46,077 --> 01:01:47,578
Is anyone here?

1719
01:01:47,662 --> 01:01:48,705
If you are,

1720
01:01:49,455 --> 01:01:52,291
could you come out to the center
and wave your hand or something?

1721
01:01:52,875 --> 01:01:54,794
EMPTY

1722
01:01:55,378 --> 01:01:58,339
Well, this is a first.
They completely blew us off.

1723
01:01:58,423 --> 01:02:01,926
I mean, we clearly said
we'd announce lights out in 30 minutes.

1724
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:03,553
All right.

1725
01:02:03,636 --> 01:02:07,515
According to the rules of Jae-seok's B&B,
we'll be turning the lights out…

1726
01:02:07,598 --> 01:02:11,352
- Who are you talking to?
- Well, we still have to do this properly.

1727
01:02:11,436 --> 01:02:12,603
Lights out.

1728
01:02:14,856 --> 01:02:16,065
- Who's that?
- Where were you?

1729
01:02:17,108 --> 01:02:18,276
Oh, you're here.

1730
01:02:18,359 --> 01:02:19,694
Did you hear the announcement?

1731
01:02:20,194 --> 01:02:21,696
Did you hear the announcement?

1732
01:02:22,363 --> 01:02:23,990
Oh, are you going to bed?

1733
01:02:24,532 --> 01:02:25,533
Then what?

1734
01:02:25,616 --> 01:02:27,452
- You're going out?
- After the announcement?

1735
01:02:27,535 --> 01:02:28,536
PERSISTENT, OBSESSIVE

1736
01:02:28,619 --> 01:02:30,079
Oh. All right, then.

1737
01:02:30,872 --> 01:02:35,126
You all did great work on the first day
here at Jae-seok's B&B.

1738
01:02:35,209 --> 01:02:38,129
We'll see you all tomorrow morning.

1739
01:02:38,212 --> 01:02:39,756
Lights out now.

1740
01:02:39,839 --> 01:02:41,841
Lights out. See you tomorrow.

1741
01:02:41,924 --> 01:02:43,593
GOOD NIGHT

1742
01:02:43,676 --> 01:02:45,470
I'll go turn off the lights.

1743
01:02:46,137 --> 01:02:48,806
Oh, you have to do them yourself?
They're not automatic?

1744
01:02:48,890 --> 01:02:50,933
They don't go out automatically. Jeez.

1745
01:02:53,603 --> 01:02:55,980
Well, they set up the beds really nicely.

1746
01:02:58,107 --> 01:02:59,609
They got water and everything.

1747
01:03:00,276 --> 01:03:02,945
Oh, look, hyung.
Everyone really made themselves at home.

1748
01:03:07,116 --> 01:03:09,118
THE LIGHTS GO OUT

1749
01:03:11,788 --> 01:03:14,499
AND THE MOON COMES DOWN

1750
01:03:15,666 --> 01:03:17,084
FIRST NIGHT LIGHTS-OUT COMPLETE
(THOUGH NO ONE'S HERE)

1751
01:03:17,168 --> 01:03:18,795
Whoa, hyung,
it really looks like the moon.

1752
01:03:19,378 --> 01:03:21,297
All right, the staff should have
a quick chat.

1753
01:03:21,881 --> 01:03:23,216
- Ye-eun.
- Yeah?

1754
01:03:23,299 --> 01:03:24,467
THE DAY ISN'T OVER YET

1755
01:03:25,718 --> 01:03:26,719
Come here.

1756
01:03:29,514 --> 01:03:30,598
- Whoa.
- What's that?

1757
01:03:30,681 --> 01:03:32,391
- A mask?
- A mask.

1758
01:03:32,475 --> 01:03:34,393
- For only part of your face?
- I'm an actress.

1759
01:03:34,894 --> 01:03:35,895
An actress?

1760
01:03:36,896 --> 01:03:38,147
I'm an actress.

1761
01:03:38,231 --> 01:03:39,899
But do you have to…

1762
01:03:39,982 --> 01:03:41,943
- I do it daily, yeah.
- Daily?

1763
01:03:42,026 --> 01:03:43,903
Well, let's sit down first.

1764
01:03:43,986 --> 01:03:45,780
Good work today, everyone.

1765
01:03:45,863 --> 01:03:47,031
How'd it go for you today?

1766
01:03:47,114 --> 01:03:49,909
Does anyone have any suggestions
or things you'd like to share?

1767
01:03:50,409 --> 01:03:51,619
I honestly had a great time.

1768
01:03:51,702 --> 01:03:53,830
- Yeah?
- The one thing I'd say is I actually wish

1769
01:03:53,913 --> 01:03:55,331
we could talk more with the guests.

1770
01:03:55,414 --> 01:03:58,584
There were moments we were so busy
we couldn't talk to them at all.

1771
01:03:58,668 --> 01:03:59,669
- So that was…
- That's okay.

1772
01:03:59,752 --> 01:04:01,045
- Oh, okay.
- It's okay.

1773
01:04:01,587 --> 01:04:04,006
This is similar
to what Woo-seok just said,

1774
01:04:04,090 --> 01:04:07,510
but I wish we'd had more
physical interaction with the guests.

1775
01:04:08,135 --> 01:04:10,555
Yeah, I mean, today,
we started a bit late.

1776
01:04:10,638 --> 01:04:11,639
Yeah, right.

1777
01:04:11,722 --> 01:04:14,684
We also had our first meal
just among ourselves, so there's that,

1778
01:04:14,767 --> 01:04:17,728
but there are bound to be some issues
as we figure things out.

1779
01:04:17,812 --> 01:04:18,938
Yeah.

1780
01:04:19,021 --> 01:04:20,481
- Like the snack bar…
- Wait.

1781
01:04:20,565 --> 01:04:22,024
- What?
- Wait, why…

1782
01:04:22,108 --> 01:04:23,901
- Wait.
- What is it, Ye-eun?

1783
01:04:23,985 --> 01:04:26,821
Chief, come on.
We can't just let this slide.

1784
01:04:26,904 --> 01:04:29,699
I mean, because… What's funny about this?

1785
01:04:29,782 --> 01:04:32,660
- We're all being serious right now.
- Wait, Ye-eun. Why are you laughing?

1786
01:04:34,036 --> 01:04:35,746
He looks so funny.

1787
01:04:35,830 --> 01:04:37,665
- Sorry.
- He looks funny?

1788
01:04:38,457 --> 01:04:40,209
- What is she talking about?
- No.

1789
01:04:40,793 --> 01:04:43,212
- Mr. EP?
- Yeah. His earrings…

1790
01:04:45,631 --> 01:04:47,383
All right, well…

1791
01:04:47,466 --> 01:04:49,677
Hold on. So, can I finish, or…

1792
01:04:49,760 --> 01:04:52,555
- I got cut off just now.
- Oh, well, what did you want to say?

1793
01:04:52,638 --> 01:04:54,891
- So, we get up early tomorrow, right?
- Yeah.

1794
01:04:54,974 --> 01:04:58,060
We'll make everyone breakfast,
then we get some free time?

1795
01:04:58,728 --> 01:04:59,937
I don't think…

1796
01:05:00,479 --> 01:05:01,480
Yeah.

1797
01:05:01,564 --> 01:05:03,900
- There's too much to do in the morning.
- Right.

1798
01:05:03,983 --> 01:05:06,402
- Yeah.
- I think we can have breakfast at 8 a.m.

1799
01:05:06,485 --> 01:05:08,654
Clean up should wrap up
around 9 a.m, right?

1800
01:05:09,363 --> 01:05:12,241
But I'm pretty sure that's when
we have to start prepping lunch.

1801
01:05:13,784 --> 01:05:15,119
Oh, right.

1802
01:05:16,537 --> 01:05:17,538
SNORT

1803
01:05:18,581 --> 01:05:20,416
Is this supposed to be like this?

1804
01:05:20,499 --> 01:05:22,960
- Seriously.
- You turn around and it's time to eat.

1805
01:05:24,337 --> 01:05:25,463
Are you crying?

1806
01:05:28,466 --> 01:05:29,550
You're not crying, right?

1807
01:05:30,134 --> 01:05:32,553
Now these are the registration forms.

1808
01:05:32,637 --> 01:05:34,430
- Hey, you know Hyo-lim?
- Yeah.

1809
01:05:34,513 --> 01:05:36,682
- The one with the killer dance moves?
- Yeah.

1810
01:05:36,766 --> 01:05:39,936
She started college during the pandemic,
so she never got to go on a retreat.

1811
01:05:40,019 --> 01:05:41,687
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1812
01:05:41,771 --> 01:05:44,899
So one of the things she wants to do here
is a dance initiation.

1813
01:05:44,982 --> 01:05:47,026
So that's why she was dancing earlier.

1814
01:05:47,109 --> 01:05:48,569
Wow, Hyeong-seon?

1815
01:05:48,653 --> 01:05:51,572
Oh, "work and childcare."
Oh, she's married.

1816
01:05:51,656 --> 01:05:54,325
I guess she's just swamped
with parenting these days.

1817
01:05:55,117 --> 01:05:57,828
Hey, guess what Dong-geon wrote
as his concern.

1818
01:05:57,912 --> 01:06:00,206
"Things might get even more awkward
with my sister."

1819
01:06:00,289 --> 01:06:02,041
THINGS MIGHT GET EVEN
MORE AWKWARD WITH MY SISTER

1820
01:06:02,124 --> 01:06:03,751
- That must be real.
- I noticed you're avoiding him.

1821
01:06:03,834 --> 01:06:06,170
Is that right?
It's kind of uncomfortable for us too.

1822
01:06:06,837 --> 01:06:09,215
You have siblings, right?
You know how it is.

1823
01:06:09,298 --> 01:06:10,841
I talk to my sister a lot.

1824
01:06:10,925 --> 01:06:12,843
Well, there are siblings like that,

1825
01:06:12,927 --> 01:06:15,262
and then there are
siblings like us. Right?

1826
01:06:15,346 --> 01:06:16,722
Good work, everyone.

1827
01:06:16,806 --> 01:06:18,057
- Good job.
- Good work.

1828
01:06:18,140 --> 01:06:19,141
THE LATE-NIGHT MEETING ENDS

1829
01:06:19,225 --> 01:06:21,352
Look, everyone's still there.

1830
01:06:21,435 --> 01:06:22,937
- Aw, they're still so young.
- Wow.

1831
01:06:23,020 --> 01:06:24,105
BUT THE AFTER-PARTY CONTINUES

1832
01:06:24,188 --> 01:06:25,398
Endless energy.

1833
01:06:26,232 --> 01:06:28,067
MEANWHILE IN THE DINING AREA

1834
01:06:28,150 --> 01:06:30,319
- I had a blast with all the games today.
- It was really fun.

1835
01:06:30,403 --> 01:06:31,779
STILL TALKING ABOUT THE QUIZ

1836
01:06:31,862 --> 01:06:34,782
The delivery box at the end was
the funniest. Everyone was like…

1837
01:06:34,865 --> 01:06:36,701
Yeah, it was so crazy.

1838
01:06:37,994 --> 01:06:39,203
Oh, it's midnight.

1839
01:06:39,286 --> 01:06:40,788
Let's wrap it up, shall we?

1840
01:06:41,372 --> 01:06:43,457
BEDTIME FOR REAL

1841
01:06:46,752 --> 01:06:49,130
ONCE ALL THE LIGHTS GO OUT

1842
01:06:50,423 --> 01:06:53,092
THE STAFF ALSO
GETS READY FOR BED

1843
01:06:54,427 --> 01:06:56,637
THEY CAN'T HELP BUT GROAN

1844
01:06:56,721 --> 01:06:58,055
Oh, I'm so tired.

1845
01:06:58,139 --> 01:06:59,348
THEIR 1ST NIGHT
AT THE B&B DEEPENS

1846
01:06:59,432 --> 01:07:00,933
Oh, boy.

1847
01:07:01,017 --> 01:07:03,436
EVERYONE IS SOUND ASLEEP
AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

1848
01:07:03,519 --> 01:07:05,354
<i>Please save me! </i>

1849
01:07:05,438 --> 01:07:07,064
- <i>Please save me!</i>
- Good morning.

1850
01:07:07,148 --> 01:07:10,693
<i>If you don't save me</i>
<i>The hunter will shoot me, bang! </i>

1851
01:07:10,776 --> 01:07:13,070
Good morning, everyone.
We've got a little surprise for you.

1852
01:07:13,154 --> 01:07:14,530
WOW

1853
01:07:14,613 --> 01:07:15,906
Good morning!

1854
01:07:15,990 --> 01:07:17,241
Please save me!

1855
01:07:17,324 --> 01:07:18,367
No, please save me.

1856
01:07:18,451 --> 01:07:19,994
WHERE PEOPLE BEG FOR THEIR LIVES

1857
01:07:20,077 --> 01:07:21,328
Please save me!

1858
01:07:21,412 --> 01:07:22,872
Comrade, save me.

1859
01:07:22,955 --> 01:07:26,876
THE TERRIFYING DAY 2
AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B BEGINS

1860
01:07:26,959 --> 01:07:29,253
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!
